                <h1>Understanding Diabetes: Causes, Symptoms, & Management</h1>
                <p>Diabetes is a chronic condition that occurs when the body either can't produce enough insulin or can't effectively use the insulin it produces. This leads to elevated blood sugar levels, which can cause various health complications. There are two main types: Type 1, which is usually diagnosed in children, and Type 2, more common in adults.</p>
